oposed size for the subview. In OpenSwiftUI,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"views choose their own size, but can take a size proposal from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their parent view into account when doing so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"proposal"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","text":"Return Value"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ViewDimensions","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance that includes a height"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and width, as well as a set of alignment guides."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call this method to ask a subview of a custom "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"about its size and alignment properties. You can call it from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your implementation of any of that protocol’s methods, like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/placeSubviews(in:proposal:subviews:cache:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Layout\/sizeThatFits(proposal:subviews:cache:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", to get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information for your layout calculations."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you call this method, you propose a size using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"